NGS Pipeline Docker Image

A ready-to-use Docker image for running Next-Generation Sequencing (NGS) analysis pipelines in a reproducible, scalable, and portable environment.

This image bundles commonly used bioinformatics tools and dependencies required for end-to-end genomic data processing, eliminating the need for complex local installations.
Use Cases
Whole genome / exome sequencing analysis
RNA-Seq data processing
Variant calling pipelines
Quality control and preprocessing of sequencing data
Bioinformatics workflow automation
🛠️ Getting Started
Pull the Image
docker pull kartzz/ngspipeline:latest
Run the Container
docker run -it --rm kartzz/ngspipeline:latest
Mount Local Data
docker run -it --rm \
  -v $(pwd)/data:/data \
  kartzz/ngspipeline:latest
⚙️ Pipeline Components

Typical tools and utilities included (may vary by tag):

Quality control (e.g., FastQC)
Read trimming and filtering
Alignment tools (e.g., BWA, Bowtie2)
SAM/BAM processing (e.g., SAMtools)
Variant calling tools
Python/R environments for downstream analysis
Directory Structure
Path	Description
/data	Input/output data directory
/tools	Installed bioinformatics tools
/scripts	Pipeline scripts
Workflow Integration

This image can be used with:

Docker Compose
Workflow managers (Nextflow, Snakemake)
Kubernetes-based pipelines
CI/CD pipelines for bioinformatics automation
 Customization

You can extend this image by:

Adding additional tools
Modifying pipeline scripts
Installing custom dependencies

Example:

FROM kartzz/ngspipeline:latest

RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y <your-tool>
